From e6e2671506de0eb7b3ef827f9deef967141f5315 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex Angel <aangeletakis@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 00:05:25 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[clang]=20std::fetch:=20=5F=5Fbuiltin=5Fstd=5Ff?=
 =?UTF-8?q?etch=20=E2=80=94=20compile-time=20URL=20fetch-and-embed?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

std::embed's sibling: given a URL, perform an HTTP(S) GET DURING CONSTANT
EVALUATION and embed the response bytes into the binary, the same way
__builtin_std_embed embeds a file.

- Builtins.td StdFetch (Consteval, variadic); Sema BuiltinStdFetch mirrors
  BuiltinStdEmbed's arg inspection (locus, status&, size&, ptr&, url_size,
  url_ptr) plus an optional trailing (hash_size, hash_ptr) pair for a
  content-hash pin; result type = the pointer arg type.
- ExprConstant.cpp BI__builtin_std_fetch reuses embed's string
  reconstruction and StringLiteral::Create/addArray byte materialization;
  the middle is replaced by: (a) an allow-list check, (b) an
  llvm::HTTPClient GET into an owned buffer, (c) optional SHA-256 verify.
  Status codes Ok/NotAuthorized/FetchFailed/Empty/HashMismatch, written to
  the caller's int& like embed's FileFoundButNotDependedOn. No caching:
  every build fetches.
- Authorization: --fetch-allow=<url-glob> (Options.td, CompilerInvocation,
  driver forward) feeds clang/Basic/FetchAllowList (URL glob -> regex; *
  within a path segment, ** across '/'). Un-allowed URL -> NotAuthorized.
- Networking: the in-tree llvm::HTTPClient (LLVMHTTP, curl/WinHTTP, HTTPS,
  redirects) - no foreign dependency. Linked into clangAST + the clang
  tool; HTTPClient::initialize() runs once in cc1_main before threads.
  isAvailable()/IsInitialized gate a clean diagnostic when built w/o curl.
- build.sh: -DLLVM_ENABLE_CURL=ON.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
